                            <comment id="14270464" author="junrao" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2015 02:53:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29751/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29751/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch origin/0.8.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14271595" author="nehanarkhede" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2015 17:48:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=junrao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;junrao&quot;&gt;junrao&lt;/a&gt; Why is this a blocker?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14271670" author="junrao" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2015 18:39:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because it doesn&apos;t match the spec of the protocol. If you pass in one partition in the request, you are expected to get only one partition in the response.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14271764" author="junrao" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2015 19:34:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review. Committed to both 0.8.2 and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
